  "prompt": "Are grapes bad for any breeds of dogs?",
  "response": "Yes, grapes and raisins are toxic to all dogs, regardless of breed. Ingesting even small amounts can cause serious health issues, including kidney failure. Symptoms of grape or raisin toxicity in dogs can include vomiting, diarrhea, lethargy, and abdominal pain. If you suspect your dog has ingested grapes or raisins, it's important to seek veterinary care immediately.",
